"content": "You are absolutely correct. The terminology was confusing and led to the previous errors. Let's clarify the coordinate system and terminology for the rest of the implementation:

### [b]Corrected Coordinate System & Terminology[/b]

-   **[b]Blueprint Orientation[/b]:]
    -   **[color=red][b]Positive X[/b][/color] = [b]Up[/b] on the blueprint (Length)
    -   **[color=blue][b]Positive Z[/b][/color] = [b]Right[/b] on the blueprint (Width)
    -   **[color=green][b]Positive Y[/b][/color] = [b]Vertical/Up[/b] in 3D space (Height)

-   **[b]Terminology[/b]:]
    -   **[b]Length[/b]:] Dimension along the **X-axis** (Up on blueprint).
    -   **[b]Width[/b]:] Dimension along the **Z-axis** (Right on blueprint).
    -   **[b]Height[/b]:] Dimension along the **Y-axis** (Vertical).

-   **[b]Wall Construction[/b]:]
    -   Walls are defined by their position in the **X-Z plane** (horizontal blueprint coordinates).
    -   Wall **thickness** is along the axis perpendicular to the wall's length in the X-Z plane.
    -   Wall **height** is always along the Y-axis.

